  "text": "We have previously found that rHDL augments VEGF levels in ischemic hindlimbs in young mice [CITATION_1] . This study, however, found that mRNA levels of VEGF were significantly lower in the hindlimbs of mice infused with rHDL and there was no change in hindlimb VEGF protein. The end points in our previous studies was 10 or 14 days. It is possible therefore that our results for VEGF expression in aged mice may indicate that rHDLinduced increases in hindlimb VEGF occur earlier postligation than at the 21 day time point at which they were measured.",
